('Lisinopril', 'Cardiovascular', 'Lisinopril is an ACE inhibitor used for hypertension, heart failure, and post-MI. It blocks angiotensin-converting enzyme, reducing angiotensin II production.', '10-40mg once daily', 'Cough, dizziness, hyperkalemia, angioedema, renal impairment', 4.7, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'AstraZeneca', 'ACE Inhibitor', 'D', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '12 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'None', 'Renal', 7654, '["Diuretics","Potassium supplements","NSAIDs","Lithium"]', '["Angioedema","Hyperkalemia","Renal impairment","Pregnancy risk"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
