('Metoprolol', 'Cardiovascular', 'Metoprolol is a beta-blocker used for hypertension, angina, and heart failure. It blocks beta-1 adrenergic receptors in the heart.', '25-100mg twice daily, 50-200mg once daily for extended release', 'Fatigue, dizziness, bradycardia, hypotension, bronchospasm', 4.6, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'AstraZeneca', 'Beta-Blocker', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '3-7 hours', '1-2 hours', '12-24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 5432, '["Verapamil","Diltiazem","Digoxin","Cimetidine","Insulin"]', '["Bradycardia","Bronchospasm","Hypoglycemia masking"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
