('Simvastatin', 'Cardiovascular', 'Simvastatin is a statin used for hyperlipidemia and cardiovascular risk reduction. It inhibits HMG-CoA reductase.', '10-40mg once daily (evening)', 'Muscle pain, elevated liver enzymes, myopathy, diabetes risk', 4.6, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Merck', 'Statin', 'X', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '2-3 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 7654, '["Cyclosporine","Fibrates","Azole antifungals","Grapefruit juice"]', '["Myopathy","Hepatotoxicity","Avoid grapefruit juice"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
