('Albuterol', 'Respiratory', 'Albuterol is a short-acting beta-2 agonist bronchodilator used for asthma and COPD. It relaxes bronchial smooth muscle by activating beta-2 receptors.', '2 puffs every 4-6 hours, nebulizer 2.5mg 3-4 times daily, max 12 puffs daily', 'Tremor, tachycardia, headache, nervousness, palpitations, hypokalemia', 4.7, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'GlaxoSmithKline', 'Beta-2 Agonist', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '4-6 hours', '5-15 min', '4-6 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 8765, '["Beta-blockers","Diuretics","Digoxin","MAOIs","TCAs"]', '["Tachycardia","Tremor","Hypokalemia","Use with caution in cardiac patients"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
