('Budesonide', 'Respiratory', 'Budesonide is an inhaled corticosteroid used for asthma and COPD. It reduces airway inflammation with a favorable safety profile.', '1-2 puffs twice daily, 80-160mcg', 'Hoarseness, oral thrush, cough, pharyngitis, adrenal suppression (high doses)', 4.6, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'AstraZeneca', 'Inhaled Corticosteroid', 'B', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '2-3 hours', '1-2 hours', '12 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 5432, '["Ketoconazole","Ritonavir","Strong CYP3A4 inhibitors"]', '["Oral thrush","Hoarseness","Rinse mouth after use","Adrenal suppression"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
