('Theophylline', 'Respiratory', 'Theophylline is a methylxanthine bronchodilator used for asthma and COPD. It relaxes bronchial smooth muscle and has anti-inflammatory effects.', '100-400mg every 6-8 hours, extended release 300-600mg once daily', 'Nausea, tachycardia, arrhythmias, seizures, insomnia, tremor', 4.2, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Methylxanthine', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '8-12 hours', '1-2 hours', '6-8 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 3456, '["Cimetidine","Erythromycin","Quinolones","Beta-blockers"]', '["Narrow therapeutic index","Monitor levels","Seizures","Arrhythmias"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
