('Cetirizine', 'Allergy', 'Cetirizine is a second-generation antihistamine used for allergic rhinitis and urticaria. It is a selective H1 receptor antagonist with low sedation.', '5-10mg once daily', 'Drowsiness (mild), dry mouth, fatigue, headache, dizziness', 4.6, '$$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Johnson & Johnson', 'Antihistamine (Second Generation)', 'B', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '8-10 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 8765, '["CNS depressants","Alcohol","MAOIs"]', '["Renal adjustment","Sedation","Avoid with CNS depressants"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Loratadine', 'Allergy', 'Loratadine is a second-generation antihistamine used for allergic rhinitis and urticaria. It is a non-sedating H1 receptor antagonist.', '10mg once daily', 'Headache, dry mouth, fatigue, nausea, dizziness', 4.5, '$$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Bayer', 'Antihistamine (Second Generation)', 'B', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '8-12 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 7654, '["CNS depressants","Alcohol","MAOIs"]', '["Hepatic adjustment","Avoid with CNS depressants"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Fexofenadine', 'Allergy', 'Fexofenadine is a second-generation antihistamine used for allergic rhinitis and urticaria. It is a non-sedating H1 receptor antagonist with rapid onset.', '60mg twice daily or 180mg once daily', 'Headache, dry mouth, nausea, dizziness, fatigue', 4.7, '$$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Sanofi', 'Antihistamine (Second Generation)', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '14.4 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 8765, '["Antacids","Aluminum","Calcium","Magnesium"]', '["Take on empty stomach","Avoid with fruit juice","Renal adjustment"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Diphenhydramine', 'Allergy', 'Diphenhydramine is a first-generation antihistamine used for allergic reactions, motion sickness, and insomnia. It causes significant sedation.', '25-50mg every 4-6 hours, max 300mg daily', 'Drowsiness, dry mouth, blurred vision, urinary retention, confusion, dizziness', 4.3, '$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Johnson & Johnson', 'Antihistamine (First Generation)', 'B', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '4-8 hours', '15-30 min', '4-6 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 6543, '["CNS depressants","Alcohol","MAOIs","Anticholinergics"]', '["Significant sedation","Anticholinergic effects","Avoid in elderly"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Chlorpheniramine', 'Allergy', 'Chlorpheniramine is a first-generation antihistamine used for allergic rhinitis and urticaria. It causes moderate sedation.', '4mg every 4-6 hours, max 24mg daily', 'Drowsiness, dry mouth, blurred vision, urinary retention, confusion', 4.2, '$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Schering-Plough', 'Antihistamine (First Generation)', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '20-30 hours', '30-60 min', '4-6 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 5432, '["CNS depressants","Alcohol","MAOIs","Anticholinergics"]', '["Sedation","Anticholinergic effects","Avoid in elderly"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Levocetirizine', 'Allergy', 'Levocetirizine is a second-generation antihistamine used for allergic rhinitis and urticaria. It is the active enantiomer of cetirizine.', '2.5-5mg once daily', 'Drowsiness (mild), dry mouth, fatigue, headache, dizziness', 4.6, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'UCB Pharma', 'Antihistamine (Second Generation)', 'B', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '8-10 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 6543, '["CNS depressants","Alcohol","MAOIs"]', '["Renal adjustment","Sedation","Avoid with CNS depressants"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Desloratadine', 'Allergy', 'Desloratadine is a second-generation antihistamine used for allergic rhinitis and urticaria. It is the active metabolite of loratadine.', '5mg once daily', 'Headache, dry mouth, fatigue, nausea, dizziness', 4.5, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'Schering-Plough', 'Antihistamine (Second Generation)', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '27 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 5432, '["CNS depressants","Alcohol","MAOIs"]', '["Hepatic adjustment","Avoid with CNS depressants"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Fluticasone Nasal', 'Allergy', 'Fluticasone nasal spray is a corticosteroid used for allergic rhinitis. It reduces nasal inflammation and congestion.', '2 sprays each nostril once daily, max 4 sprays daily', 'Nasal irritation, nosebleeds, headache, pharyngitis, epistaxis', 4.7, '$$$', 'Over-the-counter', 'GlaxoSmithKline', 'Intranasal Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '10 hours', '12-24 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 6543, '["Ketoconazole","Ritonavir","Strong CYP3A4 inhibitors"]', '["Nasal irritation","Nosebleeds","Use regularly for full effect"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Mometasone Nasal', 'Allergy', 'Mometasone nasal spray is a corticosteroid used for allergic rhinitis. It reduces nasal inflammation and congestion.', '2 sprays each nostril once daily, max 4 sprays daily', 'Nasal irritation, nosebleeds, headache, pharyngitis, epistaxis', 4.6, '$$$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Merck', 'Intranasal Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '5 hours', '12-24 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 5432, '["Ketoconazole","Ritonavir","Strong CYP3A4 inhibitors"]', '["Nasal irritation","Nosebleeds","Use regularly for full effect"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Budesonide Nasal', 'Allergy', 'Budesonide nasal spray is a corticosteroid used for allergic rhinitis. It reduces nasal inflammation and congestion.', '2 sprays each nostril once daily, max 8 sprays daily', 'Nasal irritation, nosebleeds, headache, pharyngitis, epistaxis', 4.6, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'AstraZeneca', 'Intranasal Corticosteroid', 'B', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '2-3 hours', '12-24 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 4321, '["Ketoconazole","Ritonavir","Strong CYP3A4 inhibitors"]', '["Nasal irritation","Nosebleeds","Use regularly for full effect"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Azelastine', 'Allergy', 'Azelastine is an antihistamine nasal spray used for allergic rhinitis. It has both antihistamine and mast cell stabilizing properties.', '1-2 sprays each nostril twice daily', 'Bitter taste, nasal irritation, headache, drowsiness, epistaxis', 4.4, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'AstraZeneca', 'Antihistamine', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '22 hours', '15-30 min', '12 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["CNS depressants","Alcohol","MAOIs"]', '["Bitter taste","Drowsiness","Use regularly for full effect"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Olopatadine', 'Allergy', 'Olopatadine is an antihistamine ophthalmic solution used for allergic conjunctivitis. It has both antihistamine and mast cell stabilizing properties.', '1 drop each eye twice daily', 'Eye irritation, headache, dry eye, bitter taste, blurred vision', 4.7, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Alcon', 'Antihistamine', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '2-3 hours', '15-30 min', '8-12 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 3456, '["No significant drug interactions"]', '["Eye irritation","Blurred vision","Do not wear contact lenses"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Epinephrine', 'Allergy', 'Epinephrine is a sympathomimetic used for severe allergic reactions (anaphylaxis). It stimulates alpha and beta receptors.', '0.3-0.5mg IM, auto-injector 0.15-0.3mg', 'Tachycardia, palpitations, hypertension, anxiety, tremor, headache, arrhythmias', 4.9, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Mylan', 'Sympathomimetic', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '2-3 min', '1-2 min', '15-30 min', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 7654, '["Beta-blockers","Digoxin","MAOIs","TCAs"]', '["Cardiac arrhythmias","Hypertension","Use only for severe reactions"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Hydrocortisone Topical', 'Allergy', 'Hydrocortisone topical is a corticosteroid used for dermatitis, psoriasis, and eczema. It reduces inflammation and itching.', '0.5-2.5% cream/ointment applied 2-4 times daily', 'Skin atrophy, hypopigmentation, telangiectasia, striae, acne, folliculitis', 4.3, '$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Pfizer', 'Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 hours', '4-6 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 5432, '["No significant topical interactions"]', '["Skin atrophy","Use lowest potency","Avoid face and folds"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Prednisone', 'Allergy', 'Prednisone is a corticosteroid used for severe allergic reactions, asthma, and inflammatory conditions. It has potent anti-inflammatory properties.', '5-60mg daily, taper dose', 'Weight gain, hyperglycemia, hypertension, mood changes, osteoporosis, immunosuppression', 4.5, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '3-4 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 7654, '["NSAIDs","Diuretics","Antidiabetics","Anticonvulsants"]', '["Adrenal suppression","Immunosuppression","Taper dose","Long-term risks"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Brompheniramine', 'Allergy', 'Brompheniramine is a first-generation antihistamine used for allergic rhinitis and urticaria. It causes moderate sedation.', '4mg every 4-6 hours', 'Drowsiness, dry mouth, blurred vision, urinary retention, confusion', 4.1, '$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Pfizer', 'Antihistamine (First Generation)', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '20-30 hours', '30-60 min', '4-6 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["CNS depressants","Alcohol","MAOIs","Anticholinergics"]', '["Sedation","Anticholinergic effects","Avoid in elderly"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Dexchlorpheniramine', 'Allergy', 'Dexchlorpheniramine is a first-generation antihistamine used for allergic rhinitis. It is a more active isomer of chlorpheniramine.', '2mg every 4-6 hours', 'Drowsiness, dry mouth, blurred vision, urinary retention, confusion', 4.2, '$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Pfizer', 'Antihistamine (First Generation)', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '20-30 hours', '30-60 min', '4-6 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 1234, '["CNS depressants","Alcohol","MAOIs","Anticholinergics"]', '["Sedation","Anticholinergic effects","Avoid in elderly"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Triprolidine', 'Allergy', 'Triprolidine is a first-generation antihistamine used for allergic rhinitis. It causes moderate sedation.', '2.5mg every 4-6 hours', 'Drowsiness, dry mouth, blurred vision, urinary retention, confusion', 4.0, '$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Pfizer', 'Antihistamine (First Generation)', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '4-6 hours', '30-60 min', '4-6 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 1234, '["CNS depressants","Alcohol","MAOIs","Anticholinergics"]', '["Sedation","Anticholinergic effects","Avoid in elderly"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Beclomethasone Nasal', 'Allergy', 'Beclomethasone nasal spray is a corticosteroid used for allergic rhinitis. It reduces nasal inflammation and congestion.', '1-2 sprays each nostril twice daily', 'Nasal irritation, nosebleeds, headache, pharyngitis, epistaxis', 4.5, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'GlaxoSmithKline', 'Intranasal Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '2-3 hours', '12-24 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 3456, '["Ketoconazole","Ritonavir","Strong CYP3A4 inhibitors"]', '["Nasal irritation","Nosebleeds","Use regularly for full effect"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Cromolyn Nasal', 'Allergy', 'Cromolyn nasal spray is a mast cell stabilizer used for allergic rhinitis. It prevents release of inflammatory mediators from mast cells.', '1 spray each nostril 3-4 times daily', 'Nasal irritation, sneezing, headache, unpleasant taste', 4.1, '$$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Pfizer', 'Mast Cell Stabilizer', 'B', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 weeks', '4-6 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["No significant drug interactions"]', '["Prophylactic use only","Take regularly for full effect"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);
INSERT INTO drugs (name, category, description, dosage, side_effects, rating, price, availability, manufacturer, drug_class, pregnancy_category, storage_conditions, half_life, onset_of_action, duration_of_action, metabolism, excretion, review_count, interactions, warnings, image_url, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES
('Levothyroxine', 'Endocrine', 'Levothyroxine is a thyroid hormone replacement used for hypothyroidism. It is the synthetic form of T4 and is converted to T3.', '25-200mcg once daily, dose individualized based on TSH', 'Palpitations, weight loss, tremors, anxiety, insomnia, tachycardia (overdose)', 4.8, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'Abbott', 'Thyroid Hormone', 'A', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '7 days', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 9876, '["Warfarin","Antacids","Iron","Calcium","SSRIs"]', '["Titrate slowly","Monitor TSH","Interactions with many drugs"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Liothyronine', 'Endocrine', 'Liothyronine is a thyroid hormone replacement used for hypothyroidism. It is the synthetic form of T3 with rapid onset.', '5-25mcg daily, dose individualized', 'Palpitations, weight loss, tremors, anxiety, insomnia, tachycardia (overdose)', 4.5, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Thyroid Hormone', 'A', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '1-2 days', '30-60 min', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 5432, '["Warfarin","Antacids","Iron","Calcium","SSRIs"]', '["Rapid onset","Monitor for tachycardia","Interactions"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Methimazole', 'Endocrine', 'Methimazole is an antithyroid medication used for hyperthyroidism. It inhibits thyroid peroxidase, blocking thyroid hormone synthesis.', '5-30mg daily, divided doses', 'Agranulocytosis, rash, GI upset, arthralgia, hepatotoxicity, hypothyroidism', 4.4, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Antithyroid', 'D', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '4-6 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 4321, '["Amiodarone","Digoxin","Warfarin","Theophylline"]', '["Agranulocytosis","Hepatotoxicity","Monitor CBC and LFTs"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Propylthiouracil', 'Endocrine', 'Propylthiouracil is an antithyroid medication used for hyperthyroidism. It inhibits thyroid peroxidase and blocks T4 to T3 conversion.', '50-100mg 2-3 times daily, max 600mg', 'Agranulocytosis, hepatotoxicity, rash, GI upset, hypothyroidism', 4.3, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Antithyroid', 'D', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '1-2 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 3210, '["Amiodarone","Digoxin","Warfarin","Theophylline"]', '["Agranulocytosis","Hepatotoxicity","Monitor CBC and LFTs"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Hydrocortisone', 'Endocrine', 'Hydrocortisone is a corticosteroid used for adrenal insufficiency and inflammatory conditions. It replaces deficient cortisol.', '20-30mg daily in divided doses, 100mg IV for adrenal crisis', 'Weight gain, hyperglycemia, hypertension, mood changes, osteoporosis, immunosuppression', 4.4, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '1.5-2 hours', '1-2 hours', '4-6 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 5432, '["NSAIDs","Diuretics","Antidiabetics","Anticonvulsants"]', '["Adrenal suppression","Immunosuppression","Stress dosing","Long-term risks"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Fludrocortisone', 'Endocrine', 'Fludrocortisone is a mineralocorticoid used for adrenal insufficiency. It increases sodium reabsorption and potassium excretion.', '0.05-0.2mg daily', 'Hypertension, hypokalemia, edema, weight gain, heart failure', 4.5, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Mineralocorticoid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '3.5 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["Digoxin","NSAIDs","Diuretics","Antihypertensives"]', '["Hypertension","Hypokalemia","Monitor BP and potassium"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Desmopressin', 'Endocrine', 'Desmopressin is a synthetic vasopressin analog used for diabetes insipidus and nocturnal enuresis. It increases water reabsorption in kidneys.', '0.1-0.4mg at bedtime, 10-40mcg nasal spray, 0.5-2mcg IV', 'Headache, hyponatremia, water intoxication, nausea, nasal congestion', 4.6, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Ferring Pharmaceuticals', 'Vasopressin Analog', 'B', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '1.5-2.5 hours', '1-2 hours', '8-12 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["NSAIDs","Diuretics","TCAs","Chlorpromazine"]', '["Hyponatremia","Water intoxication","Monitor sodium"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Octreotide', 'Endocrine', 'Octreotide is a somatostatin analog used for acromegaly, carcinoid syndrome, and VIPomas. It inhibits GH, insulin, and GI hormone secretion.', '50-200mcg 3 times daily, 20-30mg monthly (depot)', 'GI upset, gallstones, bradycardia, injection site pain, hypoglycemia, hyperglycemia', 4.4, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Novartis', 'Somatostatin Analog', 'B', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '1.5-2 hours', '30-60 min', '8-12 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["Cyclosporine","Insulin","Antidiabetics","Beta-blockers"]', '["Gallstones","Bradycardia","GI effects","Monitor blood glucose"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Bromocriptine', 'Endocrine', 'Bromocriptine is a dopamine agonist used for Parkinson\'s disease and hyperprolactinemia. It inhibits prolactin secretion.', '2.5-10mg 2-3 times daily', 'Nausea, dizziness, headache, orthostatic hypotension, hallucinations, constipation', 4.2, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Novartis', 'Dopamine Agonist', 'B', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '3-4 hours', '1-2 hours', '6-8 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 3456, '["Antihypertensives","Antipsychotics","MAOIs","Alcohol"]', '["Orthostatic hypotension","Hallucinations","Cardiac valvulopathy"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Cabergoline', 'Endocrine', 'Cabergoline is a dopamine agonist used for hyperprolactinemia. It inhibits prolactin secretion with once weekly dosing.', '0.25-0.5mg twice weekly, max 1mg weekly', 'Nausea, dizziness, headache, orthostatic hypotension, constipation, fatigue', 4.5, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Dopamine Agonist', 'B', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '65 hours', '1-2 hours', '7 days', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 4567, '["Antihypertensives","Antipsychotics","MAOIs","Alcohol"]', '["Orthostatic hypotension","Cardiac valvulopathy","Pulmonary fibrosis"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Calcitonin', 'Endocrine', 'Calcitonin is a hormone used for Paget\'s disease, hypercalcemia, and postmenopausal osteoporosis. It inhibits osteoclast activity.', '50-100 units daily SQ/IM, 200 units nasal spray daily', 'Nausea, flushing, injection site reaction, nasal irritation, hypocalcemia', 4.3, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Novartis', 'Calcitonin', 'C', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '2-3 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["Calcium","Calcitriol","Antacids","Digoxin"]', '["Hypocalcemia","Allergy","Monitor calcium levels"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Cinacalcet', 'Endocrine', 'Cinacalcet is a calcimimetic used for hyperparathyroidism and hypercalcemia. It increases calcium sensing receptor sensitivity.', '30-60mg once daily, titrate to 120mg daily', 'Nausea, vomiting, hypocalcemia, GI upset, headache, dizziness', 4.4, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Amgen', 'Calcimimetic', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '30-40 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["CYP3A4 inhibitors","CYP2D6 inhibitors","Strong CYP3A4 inhibitors"]', '["Hypocalcemia","Monitor calcium","Nausea","Drug interactions"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Methylprednisolone', 'Endocrine', 'Methylprednisolone is a corticosteroid used for inflammatory and autoimmune conditions. It has potent anti-inflammatory effects.', '4-48mg daily, IV 40-125mg for acute conditions', 'Weight gain, hyperglycemia, hypertension, mood changes, osteoporosis, immunosuppression', 4.6, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '2-3 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 6543, '["NSAIDs","Diuretics","Antidiabetics","Anticonvulsants"]', '["Adrenal suppression","Immunosuppression","Taper dose","Long-term risks"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Dexamethasone', 'Endocrine', 'Dexamethasone is a potent corticosteroid used for inflammation, adrenal insufficiency, and cancer. It has minimal mineralocorticoid activity.', '0.5-10mg daily, IV 6-10mg for acute conditions', 'Weight gain, hyperglycemia, hypertension, mood changes, osteoporosis, immunosuppression', 4.5, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'Merck', 'Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '36-54 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 5432, '["NSAIDs","Diuretics","Antidiabetics","Anticonvulsants"]', '["Adrenal suppression","Immunosuppression","Taper dose","Long-term risks"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Growth Hormone', 'Endocrine', 'Growth hormone is used for growth hormone deficiency, Turner syndrome, and chronic renal insufficiency. It stimulates growth and metabolism.', '0.02-0.05mg/kg daily, dose individualized', 'Injection site reactions, edema, arthralgia, hyperglycemia, carpal tunnel syndrome', 4.7, '$$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Novo Nordisk', 'Growth Hormone', 'C', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '2-3 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 3456, '["Corticosteroids","Glucocorticoids","Insulin","Antidiabetics"]', '["Hyperglycemia","Monitor glucose","Hypothyroidism","Intracranial hypertension"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Glucagon', 'Endocrine', 'Glucagon is a hormone used for severe hypoglycemia. It raises blood glucose by stimulating glycogen breakdown.', '1mg IM/SC/IV, 0.5mg for children', 'Nausea, vomiting, tachycardia, hypokalemia, allergic reactions', 4.8, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Novo Nordisk', 'Glucagon', 'C', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '30-40 min', '1-2 min', '15-30 min', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["Insulin","Sulfonylureas","Beta-blockers"]', '["Nausea","Hypokalemia","Use only for severe hypoglycemia"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Vasopressin', 'Endocrine', 'Vasopressin is a hormone used for diabetes insipidus, vasodilatory shock, and GI bleeding. It increases water reabsorption and vasoconstriction.', '1-4 units/hour IV, 5-10 units IM/SC', 'Hyponatremia, water intoxication, ischemia, arrhythmias, headache', 4.5, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Vasopressin Analog', 'C', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '10-20 min', '1-2 min', '1-2 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["NSAIDs","Diuretics","TCAs","Chlorpromazine"]', '["Hyponatremia","Ischemia","Monitor sodium","Use with caution"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Teriparatide', 'Endocrine', 'Teriparatide is a parathyroid hormone analog used for osteoporosis. It stimulates bone formation and increases bone density.', '20mcg once daily SC', 'Nausea, headache, dizziness, hypercalcemia, osteosarcoma (rare)', 4.7, '$$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Eli Lilly', 'Parathyroid Hormone Analog', 'C', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '1 hour', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["Calcium supplements","Vitamin D","Cardiac glycosides"]', '["Hypercalcemia","Osteosarcoma risk","Limit to 2 years of use"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Raloxifene', 'Endocrine', 'Raloxifene is a selective estrogen receptor modulator used for osteoporosis and breast cancer risk reduction. It has estrogen agonist and antagonist effects.', '60mg once daily', 'Hot flashes, leg cramps, thromboembolism, flu-like symptoms', 4.5, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Eli Lilly', 'SERM', 'X', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '27 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 2345, '["Warfarin","Cholestyramine","Antibiotics"]', '["Thromboembolism","Hot flashes","Pregnancy category X","Avoid in pregnancy"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Denosumab', 'Endocrine', 'Denosumab is a monoclonal antibody used for osteoporosis. It inhibits RANKL and reduces osteoclast activity.', '60mg SC every 6 months, 120mg SC monthly for cancer', 'Hypocalcemia, osteonecrosis of jaw, infections, skin reactions', 4.8, '$$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Amgen', 'RANKL Inhibitor', 'X', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '26 days', '1-2 hours', '6 months', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 3456, '["Calcium supplements","Vitamin D","Immunosuppressants"]', '["Hypocalcemia","Osteonecrosis of jaw","Infections","Dental exam before use"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);
INSERT INTO drugs (name, category, description, dosage, side_effects, rating, price, availability, manufacturer, drug_class, pregnancy_category, storage_conditions, half_life, onset_of_action, duration_of_action, metabolism, excretion, review_count, interactions, warnings, image_url, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES
('Tretinoin', 'Dermatology', 'Tretinoin is a retinoid used for acne vulgaris and photoaging. It promotes epidermal cell turnover and reduces comedone formation.', '0.025-0.1% cream/gel applied once daily at bedtime', 'Skin irritation, redness, peeling, photosensitivity, burning, dryness, itching', 4.7, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Johnson & Johnson', 'Retinoid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 weeks', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 8765, '["Benzoyl peroxide","Sulfur","Salicylic acid","Resorcinol"]', '["Photosensitivity","Skin irritation","Use sunscreen","Avoid pregnancy"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Isotretinoin', 'Dermatology', 'Isotretinoin is a systemic retinoid used for severe nodular acne. It reduces sebum production, inflammation, and comedone formation.', '0.5-1mg/kg daily for 15-20 weeks, max 2mg/kg daily', 'Dry skin, cheilitis, photosensitivity, hyperlipidemia, hepatotoxicity, teratogenicity', 4.8, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Roche', 'Retinoid', 'X', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '17-50 hours', '1-2 months', '6 months', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 6543, '["Tetracyclines","Vitamin A","Corticosteroids","Alcohol"]', '["Teratogenicity (pregnancy category X)","Hepatotoxicity","Psychiatric effects"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Adapalene', 'Dermatology', 'Adapalene is a retinoid used for acne vulgaris. It normalizes keratinization and has anti-inflammatory properties.', '0.1-0.3% gel applied once daily at bedtime', 'Skin irritation, redness, peeling, photosensitivity, burning, dryness', 4.6, '$$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Galderma', 'Retinoid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 weeks', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 7654, '["Benzoyl peroxide","Sulfur","Salicylic acid"]', '["Photosensitivity","Skin irritation","Use sunscreen"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Benzoyl Peroxide', 'Dermatology', 'Benzoyl peroxide is an antibacterial used for acne vulgaris. It releases oxygen radicals that kill bacteria and reduces inflammation.', '2.5-10% gel/cream applied 1-2 times daily', 'Skin irritation, redness, peeling, dryness, itching, bleaching of hair and clothes', 4.5, '$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Johnson & Johnson', 'Antibacterial', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 hours', '6-8 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 5432, '["Tretinoin","Other retinoids"]', '["Skin irritation","Bleaching","Use with caution with retinoids"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Clindamycin Topical', 'Dermatology', 'Clindamycin topical is an antibiotic used for acne vulgaris. It inhibits bacterial protein synthesis and reduces inflammation.', '1% gel/cream/lotion applied twice daily', 'Skin irritation, dryness, peeling, erythema, GI upset, C. difficile risk', 4.4, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Lincosamide', 'B', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 weeks', '6-8 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 4321, '["Benzoyl peroxide","Tretinoin","Erythromycin"]', '["C. difficile risk","GI upset","Use with caution"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Hydrocortisone Topical', 'Dermatology', 'Hydrocortisone topical is a corticosteroid used for dermatitis, psoriasis, and eczema. It reduces inflammation and itching.', '0.5-2.5% cream/ointment applied 2-4 times daily', 'Skin atrophy, hypopigmentation, telangiectasia, striae, acne, folliculitis', 4.3, '$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Pfizer', 'Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 hours', '4-6 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 5432, '["No significant topical interactions"]', '["Skin atrophy","Use lowest potency","Avoid face and folds"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Triamcinolone', 'Dermatology', 'Triamcinolone is a corticosteroid used for dermatitis, psoriasis, and eczema. It has potent anti-inflammatory and antipruritic effects.', '0.025-0.5% cream/ointment applied 2-4 times daily', 'Skin atrophy, hypopigmentation, telangiectasia, striae, acne, folliculitis', 4.5, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 hours', '6-8 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 5432, '["No significant topical interactions"]', '["Skin atrophy","Use lowest potency","Avoid face and folds"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Mometasone', 'Dermatology', 'Mometasone is a potent corticosteroid used for dermatitis, psoriasis, and eczema. It has anti-inflammatory and vasoconstrictive effects.', '0.1% cream/ointment applied once daily', 'Skin atrophy, hypopigmentation, telangiectasia, striae, acne, folliculitis', 4.6, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Merck', 'Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 4321, '["No significant topical interactions"]', '["Skin atrophy","Use lowest potency","Avoid face and folds"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Clobetasol', 'Dermatology', 'Clobetasol is a super-potent corticosteroid used for severe psoriasis, dermatitis, and eczema. It has potent anti-inflammatory effects.', '0.05% cream/ointment applied 1-2 times daily', 'Skin atrophy, hypopigmentation, telangiectasia, striae, acne, folliculitis', 4.7, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'GlaxoSmithKline', 'Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 hours', '12-24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 3456, '["No significant topical interactions"]', '["Skin atrophy","Adrenal suppression","Use for short-term only"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Fluocinonide', 'Dermatology', 'Fluocinonide is a potent corticosteroid used for dermatitis, psoriasis, and eczema. It has strong anti-inflammatory effects.', '0.05% cream/ointment/gel applied 2-4 times daily', 'Skin atrophy, hypopigmentation, telangiectasia, striae, acne, folliculitis', 4.5, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 hours', '6-8 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["No significant topical interactions"]', '["Skin atrophy","Use lowest potency","Avoid face and folds"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Desonide', 'Dermatology', 'Desonide is a low-potency corticosteroid used for dermatitis, eczema, and psoriasis. It has mild anti-inflammatory effects.', '0.05% cream/ointment applied 2-3 times daily', 'Skin irritation, mild atrophy, hypopigmentation', 4.3, '$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Corticosteroid', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 hours', '6-8 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["No significant topical interactions"]', '["Mild skin atrophy","Safe for face and folds"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Tacrolimus', 'Dermatology', 'Tacrolimus is a calcineurin inhibitor used for atopic dermatitis. It reduces inflammation by inhibiting T-cell activation.', '0.03-0.1% ointment applied twice daily', 'Burning, itching, erythema, photosensitivity, headache, flu-like symptoms', 4.6, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Astellas', 'Calcineurin Inhibitor', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 weeks', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 3456, '["CYP3A4 inhibitors","Immunosuppressants","Photosensitizing drugs"]', '["Photosensitivity","Malignancy risk","Apply at night"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Pimecrolimus', 'Dermatology', 'Pimecrolimus is a calcineurin inhibitor used for mild to moderate atopic dermatitis. It reduces inflammation by inhibiting T-cell activation.', '1% cream applied twice daily', 'Burning, itching, erythema, photosensitivity, headache, flu-like symptoms', 4.5, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Novartis', 'Calcineurin Inhibitor', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 weeks', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 2345, '["CYP3A4 inhibitors","Immunosuppressants","Photosensitizing drugs"]', '["Photosensitivity","Malignancy risk","Use for mild cases"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Salicylic Acid', 'Dermatology', 'Salicylic acid is a keratolytic agent used for acne, warts, and psoriasis. It causes shedding of the outer skin layer.', '0.5-5% topical, 17-40% for warts', 'Skin irritation, peeling, redness, dryness, burning, itching', 4.2, '$', 'Over-the-counter', 'Various', 'Keratolytic', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', 'N/A', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 5432, '["Topical retinoids","Benzoyl peroxide"]', '["Skin irritation","Avoid on broken skin","Use with caution"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Dapsone', 'Dermatology', 'Dapsone is an anti-inflammatory and antibacterial used for dermatitis herpetiformis and acne. It inhibits inflammation and has antibacterial properties.', '5-7.5% gel applied twice daily, 50-100mg oral daily', 'Topical: skin irritation, dryness. Systemic: hemolysis, methemoglobinemia, neuropathy', 4.4, '$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Sulfone', 'C', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '20-30 hours', '1-2 weeks', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 2345, '["Rifampin","Primaquine","Nitrofurantoin"]', '["Hemolysis","Methemoglobinemia","Monitor CBC","G6PD deficiency"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);
INSERT INTO drugs (name, category, description, dosage, side_effects, rating, price, availability, manufacturer, drug_class, pregnancy_category, storage_conditions, half_life, onset_of_action, duration_of_action, metabolism, excretion, review_count, interactions, warnings, image_url, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES
('Methotrexate', 'Oncology', 'Methotrexate is a chemotherapy agent and immunosuppressant used for cancer, psoriasis, and rheumatoid arthritis. It inhibits dihydrofolate reductase.', '10-25mg weekly, 2.5-5mg daily, 1-12g/m2 IV', 'Nausea, vomiting, myelosuppression, hepatotoxicity, nephrotoxicity, mucositis', 4.5, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Antimetabolite', 'X', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '3-10 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 7654, '["NSAIDs","Penicillins","Probenecid","Valproic acid"]', '["Myelosuppression","Hepatotoxicity","Monitor LFTs and CBC","Pregnancy category X"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Cyclophosphamide', 'Oncology', 'Cyclophosphamide is an alkylating agent used for lymphoma, leukemia, and autoimmune diseases. It cross-links DNA and inhibits cell division.', '50-150mg daily oral, 500-1500mg/m2 IV', 'Nausea, vomiting, myelosuppression, hemorrhagic cystitis, alopecia, cardiotoxicity', 4.4, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Baxter', 'Alkylating Agent', 'D', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '3-12 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 6543, '["Warfarin","Digoxin","Phenytoin","Corticosteroids"]', '["Hemorrhagic cystitis","Cardiotoxicity","Myelosuppression","Monitor CBC"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Doxorubicin', 'Oncology', 'Doxorubicin is an anthracycline antibiotic used for breast cancer, lymphoma, and sarcomas. It inhibits DNA topoisomerase II.', '25-75mg/m2 IV every 3 weeks, liposomal 50mg/m2', 'Nausea, vomiting, myelosuppression, cardiotoxicity, alopecia, mucositis', 4.6, '$$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Anthracycline', 'D', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '20-40 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 5432, '["Cyclophosphamide","Cardiotoxic drugs","Radiation"]', '["Cardiotoxicity","Myelosuppression","Monitor cardiac function","Lifetime limit"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Cisplatin', 'Oncology', 'Cisplatin is a platinum-based chemotherapy used for testicular, ovarian, and lung cancer. It forms DNA cross-links and inhibits DNA synthesis.', '20-100mg/m2 IV every 3-4 weeks', 'Nausea, vomiting, nephrotoxicity, ototoxicity, myelosuppression, neurotoxicity', 4.5, '$$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Bristol-Myers Squibb', 'Platinum Agent', 'D', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '2-3 days', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 5432, '["Aminoglycosides","Diuretics","Nephrotoxic drugs"]', '["Nephrotoxicity","Ototoxicity","Neurotoxicity","Pre-hydration required"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('5-Fluorouracil', 'Oncology', '5-Fluorouracil is an antimetabolite used for colorectal, breast, and head/neck cancer. It inhibits thymidylate synthase and DNA synthesis.', '500-1000mg/m2 IV daily for 5 days, topical 5% cream', 'Nausea, vomiting, myelosuppression, mucositis, diarrhea, hand-foot syndrome', 4.4, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Pfizer', 'Antimetabolite', 'D', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '10-20 min', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 4321, '["Leucovorin","Methotrexate","Warfarin","Phenytoin"]', '["Myelosuppression","Mucositis","DPD deficiency","Hand-foot syndrome"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Capecitabine', 'Oncology', 'Capecitabine is an oral fluoropyrimidine used for colorectal and breast cancer. It is converted to 5-FU in tumor tissue.', '1250mg/m2 twice daily for 14 days, 7 days off', 'Diarrhea, hand-foot syndrome, nausea, vomiting, myelosuppression, hyperbilirubinemia', 4.5, '$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Roche', 'Antimetabolite', 'D', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '45-60 min', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 4321, '["Warfarin","Phenytoin","Leucovorin","Antacids"]', '["Hand-foot syndrome","DPD deficiency","Monitor for diarrhea"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Paclitaxel', 'Oncology', 'Paclitaxel is a taxane used for breast, ovarian, and lung cancer. It stabilizes microtubules and inhibits cell division.', '175mg/m2 IV over 3 hours every 3 weeks, 80mg/m2 weekly', 'Neuropathy, myelosuppression, hypersensitivity, alopecia, arthralgia, myalgia', 4.6, '$$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Bristol-Myers Squibb', 'Taxane', 'D', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '5-20 hours', '1-2 hours', '3 weeks', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 4321, '["CYP3A4 inhibitors","CYP2C8 inhibitors","Cardiotoxic drugs"]', '["Hypersensitivity","Neuropathy","Myelosuppression","Pre-medication required"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Docetaxel', 'Oncology', 'Docetaxel is a taxane used for breast, prostate, and lung cancer. It stabilizes microtubules and inhibits cell division.', '60-100mg/m2 IV every 3 weeks', 'Myelosuppression, neuropathy, hypersensitivity, alopecia, fluid retention, nail changes', 4.5, '$$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Sanofi', 'Taxane', 'D', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '11-17 hours', '1-2 hours', '3 weeks', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 3456, '["CYP3A4 inhibitors","Cardiotoxic drugs","Antifungals"]', '["Hypersensitivity","Fluid retention","Neuropathy","Pre-medication required"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Vincristine', 'Oncology', 'Vincristine is a vinca alkaloid used for lymphoma, leukemia, and sarcomas. It inhibits microtubule assembly and cell division.', '1.4mg/m2 IV weekly, max 2mg', 'Neuropathy, constipation, alopecia, SIADH, myelosuppression (mild)', 4.3, '$$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Eli Lilly', 'Vinca Alkaloid', 'D', 'Refrigerate 2-8°C', '20-40 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Biliary', 3456, '["CYP3A4 inhibitors","Azole antifungals","Radiation"]', '["Neuropathy","Constipation","Avoid intrathecal administration"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
('Carboplatin', 'Oncology', 'Carboplatin is a platinum-based chemotherapy used for ovarian, lung, and head/neck cancer. It forms DNA cross-links and inhibits DNA synthesis.', 'AUC 5-7 IV every 3-4 weeks', 'Myelosuppression, nausea, vomiting, nephrotoxicity (mild), hepatotoxicity', 4.5, '$$$$$', 'Prescription only', 'Bristol-Myers Squibb', 'Platinum Agent', 'D', 'Room temperature 20-25°C', '2-5 hours', '1-2 hours', '24 hours', 'Hepatic', 'Renal', 4321, '["Aminoglycosides","Diuretics","Nephrotoxic drugs"]', '["Myelosuppression","Dose based on Calvert formula","Monitor CBC"]', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584308666744-24d5c474f2ae?w=300&h=300&fit=crop', true, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),
